{
  "texts": [
    "For harmlessness, 42K training examples are gathered for the context-distilled model.",
    "They are formatted similarly to the helpfulness data.",
    "We used 300 examples randomly sampled from 2K test set for testing.",
    "The BeaverTails dataset (Ji et al., 2023) is a preference dataset with labels for helpfulness and harmlessness.",
    "To improve safety alignments in RLHF, the BeaverTails dataset compiled over 330K question-answering pairs derived from prompts in the Anthropic-HH Red-Team dataset."
  ]
}